This is a C++ 2D game engine implemented using SDL3 library.

This is my first vibe coding experiment. I use my knowledge from past projects I've made (SmithNgine which C# XNA/Monogame based engine + others) so I am not starting cold. This project is implemented using Google Antigravity.

I have done zero manual code edits so far (it shows!). I will try to keep the architecture clean, resuable and extendable. 

Rembember, I am a old school coder and using AI tools is new to me so the main reason for me to do this is to learn agentic software development. The side product is "thengine" and the test game application(s).

I am working on Linux and this project has not yet been tested on Windows.

To build:
1) cmake .
2) cmake --build build

Test binaries will appear in "build/bin/" folder.

I give no guarantees, this project is evolving rapidly.
